{
  "stem": "14552.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we had-- my mother inherited some nice dishes and linens, and whatever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was made for her somewhere.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we had a nice table.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were proud of our lifestyle.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well,",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--we, the-- we-- one-- the one we went to wasn't in our section.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was on the other side of temple, there were also temples.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we did not frequent that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were religious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But my mother did not like the ultra-religious behavior.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She did not-- she would have a name for those who were overdoing it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she called them [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She didn't like [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yet, she, she would expect the boys, when they came to the house, to wear the hat.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she expected that they have respect for the religion.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But she did not-- she did not like this carrying it to an extreme.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my father, when he lived in Budapest, he had no religious affiliations.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was just not religious at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when he met my mother, she has brought him over to be a temple-goer.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he went to the rabbi in-- to sit by his right hand.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was-- he, he enjoyed that the, the, the, the people who would get together and schmooze.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a fun thing to be at the rabbi's table.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had-- we had always a visitor, or some salesman who was stuck in Munkacs and couldn't go back home, or someone who needed a Friday night or a Saturday meal.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we always had one or two people at the table.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was-- that was-- oh, that was everyone's habit there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anybody who had a home and was comfortable had made sure that they are charitable.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
